Critical program points in SafeMath
The critical program points in the SafeMath contract are at lines 4, 7, 12, and 15. These points are essential for the correct functioning of the smart contract.

require(c / a == b)
This invariant ensures that c divided by a equals b, which is critical for arithmetic correctness in the SafeMath contract.

assert(b <= a)
This invariant asserts that b should be less than or equal to a, ensuring proper handling of values within the contract's logic.

require(_to != address(0))
This invariant ensures that the recipient's address is not zero, preventing unintended transactions in smart contracts.

require(_value <= balances[msg.sender])
This invariant checks if the sender has enough balance to transfer _value tokens, ensuring proper token transfers in ERC20 compliant contracts.

require(balanceOf[msg.sender] >= _value)
This invariant checks if the sender has enough balance to transfer the specified amount of tokens, ensuring proper token transfers.

require(balanceOf[_from] >= _value)
This invariant ensures that the sender has sufficient funds before transferring tokens. It prevents underflow and maintains token integrity.

require(_value <= allowance[_from][msg.sender])
This invariant checks if the transferred amount is within the allowed value by the sender, ensuring proper approval-based transfers in ERC20 contracts.
